cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SE

This paper presents a new algorithm for evolving recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance and generalization of the evolved RNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of RNNs for time series prediction and the focus on memory structures could also place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
